The first thing you should do when you install Git is to set your user name and email address. This is important because every Git commit uses this information, 
and itâ€™s immutably baked into the commits that you start creating.

$ git config --global user.name "Upendra Chirumamilla"
$ git config --global user.email "upendra.ch123@gmail.com"

git config --global color.ui auto - This command enables command line coloring output.

In a local machine to make a working directory as repository use the below command
Git init

To create files inside a directory use the below command
Touch filename1 filename2

Git Status - This command is used to check the status of the files.

Git add filename -This command is used to add single file to the staging area.
Git add . -> This command is used to add all the files in the directory to the staging area.
Git rm --cached filename -> This command is used to unstage the file
Git rm -r cached . -> This command is used to unstage all files in the directory.
Git add -A -> This command is used to stage all the unstaged files from all the directories.

Commit is the save point.
Git commit -m "Github project" -> This command is used to commit the files from the staging area.
Git commit --amend -m "added body in main.css" -> This command is used to amend the commit message

Git log -> This command is used to track the changes.

vi filename -> and press i ->then enter the data want to change in the file-> then press escape key-> colon(:)wq - This command is used to edit a file.

Git remote add origin httpurl -> This command is used to connect with repo
Git branch -M main -> This command is used to change branch from master to main
Git push -u origin main -> This command is used to push the files.

If we got error like permission denied then follow the steps in the below url to connect github with SSH.
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh


Git branch branchname -> This command is used to create  a new branch.
Git checkout branchname -> This command is used to switch between the branches.
Git checkout - -> This command is used to switch back to previous branch.	
Git checkout -b branchname -> This command is used to create and checkout to that branch.
Git branch -d branchname -> This command is used to delete the branch.
Git pull -r origin main -> This command is used to pull the changes from main branch and our changes on top of it.
Git rebase --continue -> This command is used for rebase.

Git push -f -> This command is used for force push.


